[[File:Cèdre Gouraud.jpg|thumb]] '''Cèdre Gouraud Forest''' is a woodland area in the [[Middle Atlas]] Mountain Range in [[Morocco]]. It was named for the French general [[Henri Gouraud (general)|Henri Gouraud]]. This forest is located on [[National Route 8 (Morocco)|National Route 8]] between [[Azrou]] and [[Ifrane]].<ref>Justin McGuinness, 2003</ref> The forest is notable as a habitat for a sub-population of [[Barbary macaque]]s, ''Macaca sylvanus''.<ref>C. Michael Hogan, 2008</ref>
==See also== * [[Atlas cedar]] * [[Atlas Mountains]] * [[Mediterranean woodlands and forests]]
