'''Uri Bin Nun''' is an Israeli [[inventor]] and the current CEO of the [[Israel Electric Corporation]] succeeding Dr. Jacob Ravon on March 20, 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.globes.co.il/searchgl/Uri%20Bin%20Nun%20new%20IEC%20CEO_h_hd_1L3aoCZWsN34mC30mDpCrD30kQ7HjR000.html |accessdate=February 9, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721100718/http://archive.globes.co.il/searchgl/Uri%20Bin%20Nun%20new%20IEC%20CEO_h_hd_1L3aoCZWsN34mC30mDpCrD30kQ7HjR000.html |archivedate=July 21, 2011 }}</ref> He is a former student of [[KBY|Kerem B'Yavneh]].

Mr. Nun has applied for five patents,<ref>{{cite web |title=Uri |publisher=Patentdocs |url=http://www.faqs.org/patents/inventor/uri-7/ |accessdate=12 August 2014}}</ref> including one for a regenerator matrix<ref>{{cite web |title=Patent application title: Regenerator matrix with mixed screen configuration |publisher=Patentdocs |url=http://www.faqs.org/patents/app/20090000313 |accessdate=12 August 2014}}</ref> and one for a refrigeration device with an improved DC motor.<ref>{{cite web |title=Patent application title: Refrigeration device with improved DC motor |publisher=Patentdocs |url=http://www.faqs.org/patents/app/20080247889 |accessdate=12 August 2014}}</ref>

